title: No. 20 Bulldogs Run Down Golden Eagles
text:
No. 20 Bulldogs Run Down Golden Eagles 
By Norman Seawright III October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 7:31 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The No. 20 University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) football team defeated Minnesota Crookston for the tenth straight time in the twelve-game history between the two. 
The Bulldogs got off to a fast start, scoring in the first quarter on a Drew Bauer pass to Beau Bofferding, then on a Bauer scramble. The Bulldogs mercilessly (until the fourth quarter) defeated the Golden Eagles 66-17.
